    '<|syntax|>Write a Python function to implement merge sort<|assistant|def merge_sort(arr):\n    if len(arr) <= 1:\n        return arr\n    mid = len(arr) // 2\n    left = merge_sort(arr[:mid])\n    right = merge_sort(arr[mid:])\n    return merge(left, right)\n\ndef merge(left, right):\n    result = []\n    i = j = 0\n    while i < len(left) and j < len(right):\n        if left[i] <= right[j]:\n            result.append(left[i])\n            i += 1\n        else:\n            result.append(right[j])\n            j += 1\n    result.extend(left[i:])\n    result.extend(right[j:])\n    return result\n\nprint(merge_sort([38, 27, 43, 3, 9, 82, 10]))\n# [3, 9, 10, 27, 38, 43, 82]\n\nMerge sort: O(n log n) guaranteed, stable, great for linked lists. Uses O(n) extra space.<|end|>',

    '<|syntax|>Write a Python function to implement a sliding window maximum<|assistant|from collections import deque\n\ndef sliding_window_max(nums, k):\n    result = []\n    dq = deque()  # stores indices\n    \n    for i, num in enumerate(nums):\n        while dq and nums[dq[-1]] < num:\n            dq.pop()\n        dq.append(i)\n        \n        if dq[0] <= i - k:\n            dq.popleft()\n        \n        if i >= k - 1:\n            result.append(nums[dq[0]])\n    \n    return result\n\nprint(sliding_window_max([1, 3, -1, -3, 5, 3, 6, 7], 3))\n# [3, 3, 5, 5, 6, 7]\n\nUses a monotonic deque to track potential maximums. O(n) time complexity. Each element is pushed and popped at most once.<|end|>',

    "<|syntax|>Write a Python function to implement LRU cache<|assistant|from collections import OrderedDict\n\nclass LRUCache:\n    def __init__(self, capacity):\n        self.cache = OrderedDict()\n        self.capacity = capacity\n    \n    def get(self, key):\n        if key not in self.cache:\n            return -1\n        self.cache.move_to_end(key)\n        return self.cache[key]\n    \n    def put(self, key, value):\n        if key in self.cache:\n            self.cache.move_to_end(key)\n        self.cache[key] = value\n        if len(self.cache) > self.capacity:\n            self.cache.popitem(last=False)\n\ncache = LRUCache(2)\ncache.put(1, 'A')\ncache.put(2, 'B')\ncache.get(1)     # 'A' (1 is now most recent)\ncache.put(3, 'C') # evicts key 2\nprint(cache.get(2))  # -1 (evicted)\n\nOrderedDict maintains insertion order. move_to_end() makes an item most recent. popitem(last=False) removes the oldest.<|end|>",

