    '<|reasoning|>Write a function to find the kth largest element in an unsorted array<|assistant|Let me think about this step by step.\n\nFirst, what are the approaches?\n1. Sort and pick the kth element: O(n log n)\n2. Use a min-heap of size k: O(n log k)\n3. Quickselect (based on quicksort partition): O(n) average\n\nFor most practical purposes, the heap approach is best because it is O(n log k) and does not modify the original array.\n\nimport heapq\n\ndef kth_largest(nums, k):\n    return heapq.nlargest(k, nums)[-1]\n\nOr more explicitly with a min-heap:\n\ndef kth_largest(nums, k):\n    heap = []\n    for num in nums:\n        heapq.heappush(heap, num)\n        if len(heap) > k:\n            heapq.heappop(heap)\n    return heap[0]\n\nThe heap maintains only k elements. When it exceeds k, we pop the smallest (which cannot be the kth largest). The top of the min-heap is the kth largest. Space: O(k), Time: O(n log k).<|end|>',

